00:41.932 --> 00:46.811
- 7:45 on this beautiful, almost balmy
22nd of September in Schenectady.

00:46.978 --> 00:48.562
And it's the first day of fall.

00:48.730 --> 00:51.482
So in honor of that fact,
we have Elke Putzkammer...

00:51.650 --> 00:53.734
...professor of literature
at Union college...

00:53.902 --> 00:56.153
...to talk about autumn in poetry
and literature.

00:56.321 --> 00:58.239
- Good morning, professor.
- Hi, Alex.

00:58.407 --> 01:01.867
So, what about it? Why do
so many people write about the fall?

01:02.035 --> 01:05.579
Well, I think it's seen
as the beginning of the end, really.

01:05.747 --> 01:09.542
If the year is a life, then September,
the beginning of fall...

01:09.709 --> 01:12.962
...is when the bloom is off the rose
and things start to die.

01:13.130 --> 01:17.049
It's a melancholy month and maybe
because of that, quite beautiful.

01:17.217 --> 01:19.093
Is there something
you might read to us?

01:19.261 --> 01:21.470
Oh, I'd love to.

01:21.638 --> 01:25.516
Whoever has no house now
Will never have one.

01:25.684 --> 01:29.061
Whoever is alone will stay alone

01:29.229 --> 01:33.774
Will sit, read, write long letters
Through the evening

01:33.942 --> 01:37.445
And wander the boulevards
Up and down, restlessly

01:37.612 --> 01:39.864
While the dry leaves are blowing

01:40.031 --> 01:42.324
Goodness, that harsh, isn't it?

01:42.492 --> 01:46.662
Well, perhaps. But truthful.

01:49.249 --> 01:51.125
Mommy, done.

01:51.293 --> 01:53.252
Okay.

01:54.796 --> 01:56.088
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

01:56.256 --> 01:58.340
- I tried not to wake you.
- Well, thanks.

01:58.508 --> 02:00.843
You didn't. I just...
You know, I couldn't get up.

02:07.642 --> 02:10.186
- Caden, can you get that?
- It's Maria, I don't want to.

02:10.353 --> 02:13.481
- Caden... Oh, that's weird.
- Hey, it's me. How are you?

02:13.648 --> 02:15.858
Mommy, is something wrong
with my poop?

02:16.568 --> 02:19.820
No, honey, it's just green.
You probably ate something green.

02:19.988 --> 02:23.407
I didn't. What's wrong with me?

02:23.909 --> 02:26.744
I have to get that, Olive.
You're gonna be fine, okay?

02:26.912 --> 02:29.205
- But, Mommy...
- Yeah, I'll be right back, Olive.

02:29.372 --> 02:33.042
Oh, nothing.
Just wiping Olive's ass. You?

02:33.210 --> 02:36.754
- An earthquake in Kashmir...
- Oh, you're kidding. Holy fuck.

02:36.922 --> 02:41.008
...has killed an estimated 73,000...
- I don't feel well.

02:41.718 --> 02:43.260
Oh, my goodness.

03:03.949 --> 03:06.242
- March in Washington, D.c., today,
October 15th.

03:07.619 --> 03:10.955
- Harold Pinter died.
- Well, he's old, right?

03:11.122 --> 03:13.332
- No, wait. He won the Nobel Prize.
- Mom.

03:13.500 --> 03:15.793
- What, honey?
- Do you need to look at my poop?

03:15.961 --> 03:20.589
- You sure it's all right?
- It's fine, Olive. Just flush.

03:20.757 --> 03:23.467
What if it's alive? What if I kill it?

03:23.635 --> 03:25.844
- It's green like plants.
- It's not alive, honey.

03:26.012 --> 03:29.765
Remember the production of
The Dumb Waiter I did at Albanyfest?

03:32.060 --> 03:33.477
Have your oatmeal, honey.

03:34.354 --> 03:37.273
- I want peanut butter and jelly.
- You said oatmeal.

03:37.440 --> 03:40.818
- This isn't a restaurant.
- I don't want oatmeal.

03:40.986 --> 03:43.487
- Okay. Fine.
- Mommy, I'm sorry.

03:43.655 --> 03:48.576
They found avian flu in Turkey.
In the country Turkey, not turkeys.

03:48.743 --> 03:52.538
- Can I watch TV till school?
- In some chickens. Yeah.

03:55.125 --> 03:58.294
There is a secret something at play
under the surface...

03:58.461 --> 04:01.338
...growing like an invisible virus
of thought.

04:01.506 --> 04:03.591
But you're being changed by it...

04:03.758 --> 04:05.467
- Milk's expired.
- Okay.

04:05.635 --> 04:06.677
Jesus.

04:08.513 --> 04:10.014
- You better eat this.
- I will.

04:11.308 --> 04:12.641
Yeah.

04:13.059 --> 04:15.102
How did I guess
you'd ask me that question?

04:15.270 --> 04:17.813
Happy Halloween, Schenectady.

04:18.857 --> 04:21.190
And how long have you been
in New York for?

04:21.358 --> 04:25.195
The first black graduate
of the University of Alabama died.

04:25.363 --> 04:27.281
Vivian Malone Jones.

04:28.325 --> 04:32.036
Stroke, 63.

04:48.845 --> 04:50.638
Fuck!

04:50.805 --> 04:54.308
God! Somebody! Adele, help!

04:55.560 --> 04:58.979
- Jesus, Caden, what the fuck?
- I was shaving and the thing flew off!

04:59.147 --> 05:01.649
Oh, my God!
Jesus, look at your head.

05:01.816 --> 05:03.901
Oh, shit.

05:04.069 --> 05:06.070
Oh, God, I can't turn it.

05:06.738 --> 05:08.489
Oh, wait.

05:13.536 --> 05:16.914
- Mommy, Daddy has blood.
- Yeah.

05:17.082 --> 05:20.751
- Will there be a scar?
- Probably. It looks like a mud flap.

05:20.919 --> 05:24.213
- I prefer there not to be a scar.
- Yeah.

05:25.090 --> 05:26.173
That fellow is annoying.

05:26.341 --> 05:28.884
He's in here every week,
like clockwork.

05:29.552 --> 05:32.721
There. I think that should...
Let's see.

05:34.766 --> 05:37.601
- What?
- Change in bowel movements?

05:37.769 --> 05:40.854
It's a little more yellow than usual.
Why?

05:42.732 --> 05:45.776
Yeah, I'd like you to see
an ophthalmologist.

05:45.944 --> 05:48.278
- A neurologist?
- What? No.

05:48.446 --> 05:51.240
An ophthalmologist.
I said, ophthalmologist.

05:51.908 --> 05:53.492
Do you hear that?

05:53.827 --> 05:55.244
Yeah.

05:55.829 --> 05:59.123
And today is Tuesday.
Mommy, is today Tuesday?

05:59.290 --> 06:03.210
No, honey, today is Friday.
So, what exactly did he say?

06:07.173 --> 06:12.678
That my pupils weren't properly
opening and closing.

06:12.846 --> 06:14.138
Dilating.

06:14.305 --> 06:16.640
- No.
- Yeah.

06:16.808 --> 06:19.518
- I don't think that's what he said.
- Yes.

06:19.686 --> 06:22.229
- That's not what he said.
- Is it the bump to your head?

06:22.397 --> 06:24.022
He doesn't know. Maybe.

06:24.190 --> 06:27.317
He said he doesn't think so,
but maybe. But he doesn't know.

06:27.485 --> 06:30.988
- But maybe. Who knows?
- Okay, Jesus, Caden, I got it.

06:31.823 --> 06:34.032
- He doesn't know...
- Sorry. I'm a little anxious.

06:34.200 --> 06:36.660
- Did you have to get a shot, Daddy?
- No, honey.

06:36.828 --> 06:39.705
- It's the start of something awful.
- Do I have to get a shot?

06:39.873 --> 06:42.499
- Course not.
- Did you tell him I have green poo?

06:42.667 --> 06:44.918
- It's fucked timing.
- Call the plumber. Hey.

06:45.086 --> 06:47.129
Sorry. I have rehearsal. Fuck.

06:47.297 --> 06:51.341
- Hey, come on.
- Sorry, sorry, sorry. Everybody, sorry.

06:51.509 --> 06:53.677
How many years
until I have to get more shots?

06:53.845 --> 07:00.184
- Not for a really long time, babe.
- A million years?

07:00.643 --> 07:04.146
- Remember what Dr. Woodman said...
- Dad, what's a plumber?

07:04.314 --> 07:06.231
- He's a man...
- Or a woman, Dad.

07:06.399 --> 07:13.030
Right. He's a man or a woman
who fixes sinks and toilets and...

07:13.198 --> 07:15.240
- Do you know what pipes are?
- No.

07:15.408 --> 07:18.869
- Hey, Jim. I had an accident.
- Like to smoke out of?

07:19.037 --> 07:22.164
A different kind of pipe, honey.
All right, bye.

07:24.417 --> 07:28.378
Houses have pipes,
and they're made of...

07:28.546 --> 07:31.298
They're like tubes,
and they're behind the walls...

07:31.466 --> 07:34.593
...and they're under the floors
and everywhere.

07:34.761 --> 07:36.220
- And...
- What's the matter?

07:36.387 --> 07:38.680
- Every single where?
- It's okay, honey.

07:38.848 --> 07:41.642
They just carry water
to and from sinks and toilets.

07:41.810 --> 07:44.812
- It's like in your body. You have veins.
- Capillaries.

07:44.979 --> 07:46.688
Capillaries filled with blood.

07:46.856 --> 07:50.400
I have blood? I don't want blood.
I don't want blood.

07:50.568 --> 07:52.820
- What are you doing?
- Trying to explain plumbing.

07:52.987 --> 07:54.446
- Stop.
- I can't do this now.

07:54.614 --> 07:58.242
- Don't worry, you don't have blood.
- Don't tell her she doesn't have blood.

07:58.409 --> 08:01.245
- Caden, stop it.
- I don't want blood.

08:08.294 --> 08:10.754
Thanks for getting me in right away.

08:13.925 --> 08:17.761
- Was it the bump to the head?
- No.

08:22.308 --> 08:25.936
Could be, but I think we need
to get you to a neurologist.

08:26.104 --> 08:28.689
- Neurologist?
- It's a brain expert.

08:28.857 --> 08:30.190
I know what a neurologist is.

08:30.358 --> 08:34.443
- I thought from the way you asked...
- I just thought you said "urologist. "

08:38.866 --> 08:42.953
- Why do I need to see a neurologist?
- Just for a look-see.

08:43.955 --> 08:46.790
The eyes are part of the brain,
after all.

08:48.084 --> 08:50.460
No, that's not true, is it?

08:52.714 --> 08:58.010
- Why would I say it if it weren't true?
- It doesn't seem right.

08:58.761 --> 09:01.430
Like morally correct,
or "right" as in accurate?

09:05.810 --> 09:10.480
I don't know. Accurate, I guess?

09:12.817 --> 09:13.984
Interesting.

09:14.152 --> 09:17.070
Now, when you kick off, boy,
I want a 70-yard boot.

09:17.238 --> 09:19.239
And get right down the field
under the ball.

09:19.407 --> 09:23.327
And when you hit, hit low and hit hard,
because it's important, boy.

09:23.494 --> 09:25.913
There's all kinds of important people
in the stands.

09:26.080 --> 09:29.625
And the first thing you know... Ben?

09:30.501 --> 09:32.336
Ben, where do I?

09:33.838 --> 09:37.507
- Ben, how do I?
- Willy, you coming up?

09:38.301 --> 09:40.135
Willy?

09:40.970 --> 09:43.180
Willy, answer me.

09:43.848 --> 09:47.434
Willy! No!

09:48.353 --> 09:49.853
- Oh, Jesus, come on.
- Oh, crap.

09:50.021 --> 09:52.022
Claire, are you okay?
What's happening here?

09:52.190 --> 09:54.441
It's too late in the game
to have these problems.

09:54.609 --> 09:57.027
- I know, Caden. I'm sorry. We'll get it.
- Oh, my God.

09:57.195 --> 10:01.365
- You okay?
- Yeah, I think the wig saved my life.

10:01.532 --> 10:04.368
- Yeah.
- It's okay, honestly.

10:04.869 --> 10:06.078
That was good, Tom.

10:06.245 --> 10:07.329
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

10:07.497 --> 10:10.749
I was trying something different.
I was crashing differently.

10:10.917 --> 10:14.252
- Ambivalently.
- Yeah, I saw that. I liked it.

10:21.302 --> 10:24.221
Try to keep in mind that
a young person playing Willy Loman...

10:24.389 --> 10:28.517
...thinks he's only pretending
to be at the end of a life full of despair.

10:28.685 --> 10:31.645
But the tragedy is that we know
that you, the young actor...

10:31.813 --> 10:35.232
...will end up in this very place
of desolation.

10:35.400 --> 10:37.067
Okay.

10:40.321 --> 10:41.905
That's great.

10:42.740 --> 10:46.410
- Let's try it again. How long, David?
- I think 15.

10:49.205 --> 10:50.831
Anything?

10:52.875 --> 10:54.584
So now what?

10:58.423 --> 11:00.549
- Hey.
- Hey.

11:00.717 --> 11:04.928
- In search of the elusive signal.
- The signal's good here, oddly.

11:05.096 --> 11:08.140
- That is odd.
- I know. Cell phones, they're crazy.

11:08.307 --> 11:10.726
- See you in a few.
- Yep.

11:13.938 --> 11:18.108
Yeah, Dr. Heshborg said
I should see a Dr. Scoriano.

11:19.777 --> 11:21.737
My pupils don't work.

11:28.745 --> 11:31.413
I think I have blood in my stool.

11:34.459 --> 11:37.127
That stool in your office?

11:38.796 --> 11:42.466
- When I was pregnant with Olive.
- What was it like?

11:42.633 --> 11:46.094
I don't know. Hopeful or something.
Like something was gonna change.

11:46.262 --> 11:48.305
- Yeah, something did. No?
- Yeah.

11:48.473 --> 11:50.098
- Yeah, of course.
- I mean, bigtime.

11:50.266 --> 11:53.101
I mean, maybe not as much
as I'd hoped.

11:53.436 --> 11:55.687
I'm sorry.
That's a terrible thing to say.

11:55.855 --> 11:59.566
There are no terrible things to say
in here, only true and false.

11:59.984 --> 12:04.154
- Can I say something awful?
- Yes, please do.

12:06.407 --> 12:09.659
I've fantasized about Caden dying.

12:13.164 --> 12:15.874
Being able to start again, guilt-free.

12:16.626 --> 12:20.462
I know that's... That's bad.

12:21.506 --> 12:24.174
- Caden, does that feel terrible?
- Yeah.

12:24.342 --> 12:26.301
Okay, good.

12:43.861 --> 12:46.363
It's a nightmare in there.

12:47.198 --> 12:49.282
I'm sorry.

12:59.877 --> 13:01.920
So, I'm reading The Trial.

13:02.088 --> 13:03.547
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

13:05.174 --> 13:08.051
- You like?
- Love.

13:08.219 --> 13:11.680
I'm such an idiot
for not knowing about this book.

13:11.848 --> 13:14.808
- It's famous, as it turns out.
- Yeah.

13:15.434 --> 13:17.602
You're not an idiot.

13:20.356 --> 13:22.607
Then you say:

13:22.775 --> 13:27.904
"In fact, Hazel, you're very bright,
and I love your eyes. "

13:32.243 --> 13:35.912
- In fact, Hazel, you're very bright.
- Oh, am I?

13:36.080 --> 13:41.042
- And I love your eyes.
- Do you? Oh, you're a darling.

13:47.216 --> 13:49.301
Then what do I say?

13:49.594 --> 13:53.263
- I can't say what then you say.
- Why?

13:53.848 --> 13:56.099
Because it's dirty.

14:00.021 --> 14:02.230
Could you step out for a second?

14:02.607 --> 14:06.318
Go ahead. I've seen boy parts.

14:13.326 --> 14:18.121
- Can I take a piss in your sink?
- Yeah, sure. I guess.

14:28.716 --> 14:30.634
We're sold out.

14:30.801 --> 14:32.594
Great.

14:40.228 --> 14:42.145
Gorgeous.

14:43.648 --> 14:45.273
Thanks.

14:45.441 --> 14:49.069
- How was rehearsal?
- Awful.

14:49.237 --> 14:52.989
We have 560 lighting cues.

14:53.199 --> 14:57.160
- I don't why I make it so complicated.
- Because that's what you do.

14:57.620 --> 14:59.162
Yeah.

15:01.832 --> 15:05.877
We got through it though.
That's really pretty.

15:07.338 --> 15:10.131
Caden, I'm sorry, I...

15:13.344 --> 15:15.095
I can't come tonight. I'm sorry.

15:15.263 --> 15:18.431
I have two canvasses I have
to get ready to ship for tomorrow.

15:18.599 --> 15:20.433
- I know it sucks...
- It's opening night.

15:20.601 --> 15:24.104
I know. I wish I could come.
I would if I could.

15:24.272 --> 15:26.273
- I've gotta get ready.
- Tomorrow...

15:26.440 --> 15:29.192
I have to get ready.
I don't know what I'm gonna wear.

15:29.568 --> 15:31.861
I have to figure out
what I'm gonna wear.

15:51.757 --> 15:53.508
Hey.

16:07.064 --> 16:10.859
- Oh, boy, oh boy.
- Willy?

16:11.444 --> 16:13.903
It's all right, I came back.

16:16.574 --> 16:18.950
I hated myself tonight.

16:20.036 --> 16:22.412
- Plus, I'm so... Excuse me.
- Hey, Tom.

16:22.580 --> 16:23.997
I'm so bloated and enormous.

16:24.165 --> 16:26.708
No, you look good. You were great.
I was very pleased.

16:26.876 --> 16:29.753
- You okay?
- Sorry. A little bit of a headache.

16:29.920 --> 16:31.588
Willy Loman.

16:34.383 --> 16:37.218
I just wanted to say thank you
for everything.

16:37.386 --> 16:39.596
You've been absolutely brilliant.

16:39.764 --> 16:42.766
It's gonna be miserable
going ahead without you.

16:42.933 --> 16:46.436
- I'll be around. I'll check in.
- I'm such a baby.

16:47.063 --> 16:49.064
Okay. I'm gonna go get drunk,
that's what.

16:49.231 --> 16:53.443
Okay. Claire. Sweetheart.

16:57.406 --> 17:00.325
- Good. Good job.
- Oh, don't worry, I'll get better.

17:00.493 --> 17:03.078
- Good work.
- Don't worry, it'll get better.

17:05.623 --> 17:09.209
Hey. I figured I'd better get in fast.

17:09.377 --> 17:13.296
- Hey, you wanna sit?
- Yeah, yeah.

17:19.303 --> 17:23.807
- Where's el wife-o?
- Had to work.

17:24.141 --> 17:26.976
Her show in Berlin is in two weeks.

17:27.144 --> 17:29.145
We're gonna go there
for like a month.

17:29.313 --> 17:33.108
- Why do I like you so much?
- I couldn't begin to guess.

17:33.275 --> 17:35.110
Me neither.

17:36.320 --> 17:39.114
Do you get high, my friend?

17:41.033 --> 17:43.493
You know, sometimes.

17:44.870 --> 17:47.497
Do you want to now?
With me, in my car?

17:47.665 --> 17:50.208
I get kind of...

17:51.877 --> 17:54.295
...something when I'm stoned.

17:54.463 --> 17:57.048
What does "something" mean?

17:57.675 --> 17:59.509
You know...

18:01.220 --> 18:03.012
...bothered.

18:03.180 --> 18:06.182
- What does "bothered" mean?
- You know.

18:06.892 --> 18:10.228
Bothered. Horny.

18:13.190 --> 18:16.276
And me with a station wagon and all.
Could be dangerous.

18:16.444 --> 18:20.864
- Yeah, could be.
- You're absolutely zero fun.

18:34.378 --> 18:37.213
When are the reviews
gonna get here?

18:40.593 --> 18:42.302
Don't know.

18:47.641 --> 18:50.894
His best friends finger two babies...

18:51.061 --> 18:53.438
One this big, one this big.
- And two kittens.

18:53.606 --> 18:57.484
- Hey.
- Hi, Caden. How'd it go?

18:59.528 --> 19:00.945
- Hi.
- Hi.

19:01.113 --> 19:02.780
It's late.

19:04.074 --> 19:06.743
Maria came over
to keep me company because...

19:06.911 --> 19:09.037
And we just lost track.
I got everything done.

19:09.205 --> 19:14.292
But I'm sorry I missed your play.
I'm sorry. But how'd it go?

19:14.919 --> 19:17.045
Great. We're a hit.

19:18.047 --> 19:19.756
Reviews are great.

19:19.924 --> 19:24.427
Times said it was brilliant casting
young people as Willy and Linda.

19:24.595 --> 19:28.598
- That's great, Caden. Good for you.
- Great.

19:28.766 --> 19:32.352
I can't wait to see it tomorrow.
That's... Tonight.

19:33.479 --> 19:34.604
That's great.

19:35.397 --> 19:38.775
Wow, it's really late... Early.

19:39.360 --> 19:41.110
Early.

19:41.570 --> 19:44.572
It's late.
Hey, I would love to see it too.

19:44.740 --> 19:48.284
- Can we get Maria a ticket?
- You're stoned.

19:49.578 --> 19:52.580
I mean, a little. It's, you know...
I don't know.

19:52.748 --> 19:55.583
But are you happy with it?

19:55.751 --> 20:00.004
Yeah. Yeah, I'd love for you to see...
To know what you think.

20:00.631 --> 20:02.215
It doesn't matter what I think.

20:02.383 --> 20:07.804
Absolutely. It's all about
your artistic satisfaction, Caden.

20:17.439 --> 20:20.149
- Congratulations.
- Yeah.

20:31.412 --> 20:36.416
- I've always loved this house.
- Yes, it's a wonderful place.

20:36.667 --> 20:39.919
The truth is, I never really imagined
I could afford it.

20:40.087 --> 20:42.088
Well, the sellers
are very motivated now.

20:46.510 --> 20:52.348
It's a scary decision.
I never thought I'd buy a house alone.

20:52.516 --> 20:56.352
But, you know, I'm 36,
and I wonder what it is I'm waiting for.

20:56.520 --> 21:00.315
- Home buying is always scary.
- And with the fire and all especially.

21:00.482 --> 21:02.734
Well, it's a good size though,
2200 square feet...

21:02.901 --> 21:05.320
...not including
the partially finished basement.

21:05.487 --> 21:07.614
Oh, I don't know.

21:08.699 --> 21:12.785
- I'm thinking I should go.
- It's a perfect size for someone alone.

21:12.953 --> 21:19.500
I like it, I do. I'm just really concerned
about dying in the fire.

21:19.835 --> 21:23.129
It's a big decision
how one prefers to die.

21:23.297 --> 21:26.215
Would you like to meet my son?
Derek.

21:27.384 --> 21:30.970
Derek's living in the basement
since his divorce, if that's okay.

21:31.138 --> 21:32.847
Hey, Mom.

21:38.562 --> 21:41.439
- Let's go, Ma.
- I want just a minute.

21:49.865 --> 21:51.741
I never...

21:53.410 --> 21:57.246
Forgive me, dear. I can't cry.

21:59.625 --> 22:01.751
I don't know what it is,
but I can't cry.

22:05.047 --> 22:09.342
It seems to me
that you're just on another trip.

22:09.510 --> 22:13.096
I keep expecting you.
Why did you do it?

22:13.263 --> 22:17.266
I search and I search
and I can't understand it.

22:17.434 --> 22:21.896
I made the last payment
on the house today.

22:22.064 --> 22:26.776
We're free and clear.
We're free. We're free.

22:32.866 --> 22:35.201
- Well done.
- Bravo.

22:35.953 --> 22:40.998
- Well done. It was very successful.
- I thought it was wonderful.

22:41.166 --> 22:43.251
Why did the older people
look so young?

22:43.419 --> 22:45.962
It was a choice, Dad.
I'll explain later.

22:46.130 --> 22:51.384
I can't get excited about your restaging
someone else's old play, it just...

22:51.552 --> 22:53.094
There's nothing personal in it.

22:53.262 --> 22:55.680
People are coming out of the theater
crying.

22:55.848 --> 22:58.266
Great. Be a fucking tool
of suburban, blue-haired...

22:58.434 --> 23:00.184
...regional-theater subscribers.

23:00.352 --> 23:02.145
- You didn't you think it was long?
- No.

23:02.312 --> 23:03.771
But what are you leaving behind?

23:03.939 --> 23:06.232
You act as if you have forever
to figure it out.

23:06.400 --> 23:08.901
When you're dead, there's no time.
The world is...

23:09.069 --> 23:12.405
I don't know.
I slept maybe three hours.

23:12.573 --> 23:14.782
So we're both tired.

23:16.326 --> 23:19.495
No, I cuddled with Olive all night.
It was great.

23:24.752 --> 23:27.503
Morning. Morning.

23:28.922 --> 23:32.925
- Morning, Caden.
- I think I might have arthritis.

23:33.093 --> 23:34.635
Friends on fire.

23:37.347 --> 23:38.806
I'm going to.

23:41.185 --> 23:45.938
No, I know exactly.
Okay, I will. I'll call you later.

23:46.106 --> 23:47.356
I know. You're right. Bye.

23:50.277 --> 23:52.820
My joints are stiff.

23:55.532 --> 23:57.450
Who was that?

23:59.620 --> 24:01.829
- Maria.
- Right.

24:02.372 --> 24:05.041
Three hours since you spoke.

24:05.501 --> 24:08.878
Caden, I think I wanna go to Berlin
with just Olive.

24:11.548 --> 24:15.301
- I think it would be good for us.
- Oh, Christ.

24:15.469 --> 24:17.386
Morning, kiddos.

24:19.223 --> 24:21.724
Why don't you want me to go?

24:21.892 --> 24:27.230
You know, I think it would be a good
thing for the two of us to do alone.

24:27.397 --> 24:31.067
How do you think I'm supposed
to respond to something like that?

24:33.904 --> 24:36.739
- Want me to zip your coat up?
- Yeah.

24:41.662 --> 24:44.539
What's wrong with your face,
Daddy?

24:45.791 --> 24:47.959
It's pustules.

24:48.460 --> 24:51.170
It's called sycosis.

24:51.338 --> 24:55.424
Spelled differently than "psychosis,"
but it sounds the same.

24:55.592 --> 24:57.218
I don't know what that means.

24:57.386 --> 24:58.928
Of course not.

24:59.096 --> 25:03.140
Well, there are two kinds of psychosis.
They're spelled differently.

25:03.308 --> 25:08.020
P- S-Y is like if you're crazy,
like Mama.

25:08.981 --> 25:11.941
S- Y is like these ugly things
on my face.

25:12.317 --> 25:14.902
- You could have both, though.
- I could, but I don't.

25:24.454 --> 25:26.747
Can I ask you something, Ad?

25:30.794 --> 25:33.588
Have I disappointed you somehow?

25:34.673 --> 25:38.885
I don't know what I'm doing.
We're just spending a little time apart.

25:43.265 --> 25:45.474
We'll talk when I get back, okay?

25:49.062 --> 25:53.149
Everyone is disappointing.
The more you know someone, it just...

25:54.276 --> 25:57.987
This whole romantic-love thing,
it's just a projection anyway, right?

25:58.363 --> 26:00.531
I mean, I don't know.

26:04.661 --> 26:07.371
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

26:09.499 --> 26:11.626
I love you.

26:17.966 --> 26:21.844
I don't know what I'm doing.
I don't know.

26:29.144 --> 26:30.728
We'll talk when I get back.

26:34.441 --> 26:36.150
Okay?

26:48.163 --> 26:50.957
Flurostatin TR
allows you to live life...

26:51.124 --> 26:55.044
...when it's your turn to face
the challenges of chemotherapy.

27:10.102 --> 27:13.229
Ask your doctor
if Flurostatin TR is right for you.

27:30.539 --> 27:33.499
- And I'm on the first train
out of Palookaville.

27:33.667 --> 27:36.335
- The Miracle Brush
can scour everything from bottles...

27:36.503 --> 27:39.255
- Rise and shine...
- Lift those legs...

27:59.693 --> 28:03.320
- I'm lonely.
- Yes. Anything else?

28:04.906 --> 28:08.117
- I'm hurt.
- Yes. And?

28:13.290 --> 28:15.708
I think Adele's right.
I'm not doing anything real...

28:15.876 --> 28:17.752
What would be real?

28:17.961 --> 28:20.337
I'm afraid I'm gonna die.

28:21.423 --> 28:23.674
I don't know what's wrong with me.

28:23.842 --> 28:26.260
I wanna do something important
while I'm still here.

28:26.428 --> 28:30.806
That would be the time to do it. I have
a book that might help you get better.

28:30.974 --> 28:34.810
- Better?
- It's called Getting Better.

28:35.771 --> 28:39.106
- Who wrote it?
- I did. All of these.

28:39.274 --> 28:42.651
- Wow, I never knew that.
- Yes. Well, wow, indeed.

28:44.988 --> 28:46.822
In conclusion... Cats eat rats...

28:46.990 --> 28:50.117
Within his own plumbing...
Me who am as a raw nerve...

28:50.285 --> 28:52.828
Synthetic vaginal juices...
Substantial crease...

28:52.996 --> 28:54.663
That's $45.

29:07.469 --> 29:11.138
Five. Five.

29:12.474 --> 29:14.225
Five.

29:16.019 --> 29:18.229
Some fives. That's not good.

29:18.396 --> 29:21.357
Keep with the flossing.
We'll see you in three months.

29:21.691 --> 29:25.694
Six. Six. Six.

29:25.862 --> 29:28.531
I'm gonna recommend
you see a periodontist.

29:28.698 --> 29:30.825
He'll probably recommend
gum surgery.

29:37.082 --> 29:40.459
- Hello?
- Hey, I'm so glad I finally got you.

29:40.627 --> 29:43.754
- Hello, who is this?
- It's Caden.

29:43.922 --> 29:45.756
Ellen?

29:46.258 --> 29:49.885
It's Caden. I can't wait to see you
and Olive on the 12th...

29:50.053 --> 29:54.974
No, I have to go.
I'm sorry, there's a party. I'm famous.

29:55.142 --> 29:56.517
Have fun...

30:12.075 --> 30:14.034
911, state your emergency.

30:14.202 --> 30:16.245
- I'm sick! I'm sick!
- Ma'am?

30:40.770 --> 30:42.021
Mr. Cotard?

30:58.914 --> 31:00.998
Mr. Cotard.

31:11.092 --> 31:13.552
You've had a seizure of sorts.

31:15.931 --> 31:16.972
What does that mean?

31:17.140 --> 31:21.310
Seems to be some synaptic
degradation, fungal in origin.

31:21.478 --> 31:23.646
Autonomic functions
are going haywire.

31:23.980 --> 31:26.649
You'll lose your ability
to salivate, cry, et cetera.

31:26.816 --> 31:31.070
- Is it serious?
- We don't know. But, yes.

31:31.738 --> 31:34.073
We'll get you enrolled
in some biofeedback program.

31:34.241 --> 31:37.159
Maybe you can learn
some sort of manual override.

31:49.381 --> 31:52.341
We should get a drink.
It would be fun.

31:52.509 --> 31:58.347
- It would be weird.
- I like weird. I like you. See?

31:59.683 --> 32:02.476
Anyway, I don't wanna
make you uncomfortable, I...

32:04.688 --> 32:08.274
Okay, so I do
wanna make you uncomfortable.

32:19.577 --> 32:21.620
And what do we do with all this?

32:24.624 --> 32:28.002
You wanna come over to my place,
Cotard?

32:31.756 --> 32:35.843
I won't let you off the hook this time
by saying, "Never mind. "

32:36.011 --> 32:38.554
Adele is only on vacation.

32:38.722 --> 32:43.225
She hasn't called since she left.
It's been a year.

32:43.768 --> 32:46.020
It's been a week.

32:47.897 --> 32:50.441
I'm gonna buy you a calendar.

32:58.908 --> 33:00.826
Okay.

33:03.413 --> 33:05.456
Just for one drink.

33:09.127 --> 33:12.171
Come on. Scraps for my scrapbook.

33:16.760 --> 33:20.763
I can't... I really can't drink very much
because of my condition.

33:30.440 --> 33:32.107
Did you put something in it?

33:32.275 --> 33:36.528
If that's what it takes,
consider it done.

33:38.573 --> 33:41.658
Love potion number 69.

33:44.746 --> 33:47.206
- It's good.
- Does it make you wanna kiss me?

33:48.458 --> 33:51.919
- Kind of.
- Tell me why.

33:52.504 --> 33:55.631
Because I feel a lot of longing.

33:55.799 --> 33:58.384
Beg a girl, why don't you?

33:58.635 --> 34:00.469
- Please, Hazel.
- On your knees.

34:02.097 --> 34:03.764
What?

34:03.932 --> 34:07.768
I want you to beg me
on your knees for a kiss.

34:07.936 --> 34:09.520
Just for fun.

34:12.815 --> 34:14.315
Why am I doing this?

34:16.277 --> 34:18.152
For fun, baby.

34:21.908 --> 34:24.701
Will you help me
forget my troubles?

34:25.203 --> 34:27.079
Oh, kiddo.

34:28.998 --> 34:30.331
You don't even know.

34:34.670 --> 34:37.089
- What?
- I don't know.

34:37.424 --> 34:40.467
- What is it?
- I don't know, I'm sorry.

34:42.344 --> 34:44.221
I'm sorry.

34:46.181 --> 34:48.851
- What?
- I don't know, I'm just...

34:51.103 --> 34:54.273
I'm just really confused.

34:54.899 --> 34:56.775
I'm sorry.

34:57.694 --> 34:59.236
I...

35:03.116 --> 35:06.452
I'm really sick.

35:08.037 --> 35:10.539
And I think I'm dying.

35:12.208 --> 35:16.170
I have a kid, and I'm married.

35:21.092 --> 35:26.180
I just thought
this might change things, you know?

35:26.347 --> 35:31.059
I had a good time,
and I think you're a very nice person.

35:32.395 --> 35:36.106
That is just the wrong thing
to say right now, Caden.

35:48.578 --> 35:50.537
You should go.

35:56.461 --> 35:59.588
Hazel. Leave a message or not.
It's your dime.

36:00.173 --> 36:02.633
Hi. You know,
I haven't heard from you in a while...

36:02.800 --> 36:05.427
...and I just thought I'd call
and say hi.

36:05.595 --> 36:07.429
Hi, Hazel.

36:13.436 --> 36:16.271
Now. Now. Be here now.

36:17.357 --> 36:19.650
Olive wanted me to ask you
not to read her diary.

36:19.817 --> 36:23.403
She left it under her pillow
by mistake.

36:41.047 --> 36:43.590
Dear Mr. Cotard,
it is my pleasure to inform you...

36:43.758 --> 36:46.593
...that you have been named
a 2009 MacArthur Fellow.

36:46.761 --> 36:50.055
It is our hope that you will use
your newly found financial freedom...

36:50.223 --> 36:53.308
...to create something unflinchingly
true, profoundly beautiful...

36:53.476 --> 36:56.353
...and of unremitting value
to your community and to the world.

36:56.521 --> 36:58.355
- I got this MacArthur grant.
- Oh, Caden.

36:58.523 --> 37:01.191
- Yeah, a lot of money.
- Know what you're gonna do with it?

37:01.359 --> 37:05.737
Theater piece.
Something big and true and tough.

37:05.905 --> 37:08.156
I'm gonna finally put my real self
into something.

37:08.658 --> 37:12.578
What is your real self, do you think?

37:13.454 --> 37:15.372
I don't know yet.

37:16.666 --> 37:19.334
The MacArthur is called
"the genius grant"...

37:19.502 --> 37:21.503
...and I wanna earn it.

37:21.671 --> 37:24.298
That's wonderful. God bless.

37:24.465 --> 37:27.801
I guess you'll have to discover
your real self, right?

37:27.969 --> 37:29.511
Yeah.

37:30.722 --> 37:33.640
I wanted to ask you, how old are kids
when they start to write?

37:33.808 --> 37:36.685
There's an absolutely brilliant novel
written by a 4-year-old.

37:36.853 --> 37:40.522
- Really?
- Little Winky by Horace Azpiazu.

37:40.690 --> 37:42.316
- That's cute.
- Oh, hardly.

37:42.483 --> 37:44.901
Little Winky
is a virulent anti-Semite.

37:45.069 --> 37:48.280
The story follows his initiation
into the Klan...

37:48.448 --> 37:51.366
...his immersion
in the pornographic snuff industry...

37:51.534 --> 37:54.786
...and his ultimate degradation
at the hands of a black ex-convict...

37:54.954 --> 37:58.665
...named Eric Washington Jackson
Jones Johnson...

37:58.833 --> 38:00.792
- Written by a 4-year-old?
... Jefferson.

38:02.837 --> 38:04.087
Written by a 4-year-old?

38:04.255 --> 38:06.506
Well, Azpiazu killed himself
when he was 5.

38:06.674 --> 38:09.635
- Why did he kill himself?
- I don't know. Why did you?

38:09.802 --> 38:11.303
What?

38:11.721 --> 38:13.305
I said, why would you?

38:14.724 --> 38:16.683
Oh, I don't know.

38:19.646 --> 38:23.231
Yeah, I wanna bring my production
to New York...

38:23.399 --> 38:28.403
...to get it seen by people,
you know, who matter.

38:28.738 --> 38:31.365
- The sooner the better.
- This theater, centrally located.

38:31.532 --> 38:34.409
Heart of the theater district,
so, you know, great for plays.

38:34.577 --> 38:38.955
- Yeah?
- Oh, yeah. Absolutely. There it is.

38:40.249 --> 38:43.085
- What was this used for?
- Plays.

38:45.004 --> 38:48.674
- Like, theater plays?
- Shakespeare.

38:50.426 --> 38:52.302
King Lear.

38:52.637 --> 38:54.554
The storm.

38:55.515 --> 38:59.476
You see, the idea
is to do a massive theater piece.

38:59.686 --> 39:02.938
You know, uncompromising, honest.

39:05.024 --> 39:09.194
Here's what I think theater is.
It's the beginning of thought.

39:10.154 --> 39:12.572
It's the truth not yet spoken.

39:12.740 --> 39:16.410
It's what a man feels like
after he's been clocked in the jaw.

39:17.161 --> 39:22.082
It's love in all its messiness.

39:22.792 --> 39:26.378
You know, and I want all of us,
players and patrons alike...

39:26.546 --> 39:30.465
...to soak
in the communal bath of it...

39:30.633 --> 39:34.469
...the mikvah, as the Jews call it.

39:34.637 --> 39:40.142
Because we're all in the same water,
after all.

39:40.518 --> 39:46.648
You know, soaking
in our very menstrual blood...

39:46.816 --> 39:48.650
...and nocturnal emissions.

39:49.485 --> 39:51.945
This is what I wanna try
to give people.

39:52.405 --> 39:55.407
Okay, here you go.
Here's your salad.

39:57.785 --> 40:00.120
- Here's your soup.
- Thanks.

40:02.123 --> 40:04.541
- Thank you.
- Enjoy.

40:10.673 --> 40:14.426
- What are you doing?
- Salivating.

40:15.178 --> 40:17.679
The biofeedback training.

40:20.975 --> 40:23.518
- So I was wondering if you'd help.
- In your box office?

40:23.686 --> 40:27.606
No, as my assistant.

40:27.815 --> 40:30.484
I'm not sure I can work with you,
Caden.

40:31.903 --> 40:33.195
I'm kind of angry.

40:34.113 --> 40:36.281
I just wanna normalize it.

40:39.035 --> 40:41.578
I think we'd have a lot of fun
together.

40:55.176 --> 40:57.260
I miss you.

40:58.554 --> 41:00.806
- Really disturbing.
- I know.

41:03.726 --> 41:07.062
Dear diary, thank you
for being my new best friend.

41:07.230 --> 41:10.982
My name is Olive Cotard,
and I'm 4 years old.

41:11.150 --> 41:13.527
I like chocolate,
and my favorite color is pink.

41:17.031 --> 41:19.074
This is pink.

41:21.494 --> 41:23.829
Yeah, that's good.

41:23.996 --> 41:25.914
- Next.
- Hi.

41:33.506 --> 41:35.549
We'll start by talking honestly...

41:35.716 --> 41:39.594
...and out of that,
a piece of theater will evolve.

41:40.429 --> 41:42.097
I'll begin.

41:44.517 --> 41:46.852
I've been thinking a lot
about dying lately.

41:47.270 --> 41:51.064
- You're gonna be fine, sweetie.
- Well, I appreciate that, Claire, but...

41:51.232 --> 41:52.315
You are, you poor thing.

41:52.483 --> 41:56.987
Yeah, well, regardless of how
this particular thing works itself out...

41:57.613 --> 42:00.240
...I will be dying.

42:01.617 --> 42:03.743
And so will you.

42:05.121 --> 42:07.414
And so will everyone here.

42:11.294 --> 42:13.920
And that's what I wanna explore.

42:14.088 --> 42:16.548
We're all hurtling towards death.

42:20.511 --> 42:23.805
Yet here we are,
for the moment, alive...

42:24.515 --> 42:26.725
...each of us knowing
we're gonna die...

42:28.728 --> 42:31.438
...each of us
secretly believing we won't.

42:32.815 --> 42:34.816
It's brilliant.

42:36.277 --> 42:38.987
It's everything.

42:40.406 --> 42:42.824
It's Karamazov.

42:47.538 --> 42:49.831
- Stop.
- I'm just asking.

42:49.999 --> 42:52.667
- You're so obnoxious.
- You're so obnoxious.

42:53.336 --> 42:55.879
- You do not wanna cross me.
- Don't I?

43:01.344 --> 43:03.178
Hi, Claire.

43:04.013 --> 43:06.932
- Hi.
- Hazel.

43:07.099 --> 43:09.935
Yeah. No, no. I know, I know. Hazel.
You're the box office.

43:10.102 --> 43:12.604
- Yeah, I'm the box office.
- How are you?

43:12.813 --> 43:15.023
Wonderful. You?

43:15.191 --> 43:17.108
Yeah, yeah. I'm good. I'm fine.
Thank you.

43:17.610 --> 43:21.196
Actually, I'm meeting Caden here.
You know Mr. Cotard, right?

43:21.364 --> 43:24.115
Yes, I recall Mr. Cotard.

43:26.035 --> 43:27.243
Yeah. I'm waiting...

43:33.042 --> 43:35.502
- Hey.
- Hi, Caden.

43:35.670 --> 43:38.588
- Hi, Caden.
- Hi, Hazel. Hi, Claire.

43:38.756 --> 43:40.590
Hi.

43:40.800 --> 43:42.634
- This is Derek.
- Hi, Derek.

43:42.802 --> 43:45.553
- Hi, Derek.
- Hi, Derek.

43:45.721 --> 43:46.763
Hi.

43:50.726 --> 43:54.104
Well, we'll leave you be.
It's nice to see you again.

43:54.271 --> 43:58.066
- Take care.
- Why am I bowing? Okay, bye.

44:01.195 --> 44:04.739
- That was awkward.
- Yeah, I guess.

44:07.201 --> 44:08.243
Do you like beaver...?

44:08.411 --> 44:11.413
So could you tell me maybe
what it is that you want from me?

44:13.416 --> 44:15.750
You know, like, from my character.

44:18.045 --> 44:20.714
Well, we'll build it over time
together.

44:20.881 --> 44:23.925
You know, try to find a real person,
maybe, to model it after.

44:24.093 --> 44:26.428
That Hazel girl's
kind of interesting maybe.

44:26.595 --> 44:28.304
- You know, like, why...?
- Although...

44:28.472 --> 44:30.890
Why is she still working
at a box office at her age?

44:31.058 --> 44:33.101
I don't know.
Probably not that interesting.

44:33.269 --> 44:36.271
Maybe she wanted to be an actress,
but she lacked the confidence.

44:36.439 --> 44:38.690
- Yeah, we'll talk about it.
- I'm so excited.

44:38.858 --> 44:40.483
Really? Why?

44:42.111 --> 44:45.780
Because I think that it's brave.

44:45.948 --> 44:50.535
And I just feel like
I'm gonna be part of a revolution.

44:50.703 --> 44:53.830
I keep thinking about Artaud,
Krapp's Last Tape...

44:53.998 --> 44:57.125
...you know, and Grotowski,
for chrissake.

44:57.293 --> 44:59.419
I don't know what I'm doing.

45:00.337 --> 45:01.963
But that's what so refreshing.

45:02.131 --> 45:04.382
Knowing that you don't know...

45:04.550 --> 45:08.970
...is the first and the most essential
step to knowing, you know?

45:09.930 --> 45:11.848
I don't know.

45:16.479 --> 45:19.105
- Well, I'm proud of you.
- Thanks.

45:19.273 --> 45:21.232
- Don't say that, not to me.
- Oh, sorry.

45:23.819 --> 45:26.237
My mother died last night.

45:27.323 --> 45:32.911
Oh, my God. I'm so sorry.
What are you doing out?

45:36.499 --> 45:39.667
- This is me.
- Well...

45:40.169 --> 45:43.755
Well, it was nice meeting you.
Oh, God, did I just say "meeting"?

45:43.923 --> 45:48.927
- I'm sorry. I'm so stupid.
